italisierung: Welche Rolle spielen neue Zeitkonzepte für das Schreiben? Welche Formen der Zeitreflexion prägen Romane der letzten 15 Jahre? Welche neuen Schreibweisen werden in digitalen Medien entwickelt?  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspects. 0aLiterature and society. 0aLiterature and technology. 0aLiterature and the Internet. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aGegenwartsliteratur. 4aZeit. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / 21st Century .2bisacsh  aContemporary literature.  adigital media.  atime.1 aBalint, Lilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirnstiel, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrauthausen, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreuzmair, Elias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreuzmair, Elias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOhnesorge, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaßmann, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPflock, Magdalena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiesner, Ann-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSahner, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchumacher, Eckhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchumacher, Eckhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStubenrauch, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator